                            <comment id="14109876" author="garydgregory" created="Mon, 25 Aug 2014 22:30:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do you have an example to reproduce the problem?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14110196" author="jvz" created="Tue, 26 Aug 2014 02:46:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can think of one:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;MyMarker &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;implements&lt;/span&gt; org.slf4j.Marker {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// ...
&lt;/span&gt;}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;org.slf4j.Marker m = ...;
org.slf4j.Logger logger = ...;
logger.info(m, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;hi&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What we need is a converter from generic SLF4J Markers into Log4j Markers. We have the basic code to do this inside &lt;tt&gt;log4j-to-slf4j&lt;/tt&gt;; it just needs to be ported to &lt;tt&gt;log4j-slf4j-impl&lt;/tt&gt; as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14110239" author="jvz" created="Tue, 26 Aug 2014 03:53:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in trunk. Please verify and close. Note that if your custom marker implementation contains cycles (via children/referent markers), then you&apos;re bound to get an infinite loop. I don&apos;t think that&apos;s supported anyhow, but I could be wrong.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
